<h1>"View in GWW" bookmarklet</h1>

<p>Don't follow the link below; add it to your bookmarks. It lets you jump from a Flickr photo page to that photo's page in Guess Where Watcher, so you can see whether and how the photo has been scored.</p>

<a id="viewInGWW" href="">View in GWW</a>
<%-# http://juhukinners.wordpress.com/2009/01/08/how-to-write-a-bookmarklet/ -%>
<script type="text/javascript">
function loadViewInGWW() {
  var script = document.createElement("script");
  script.src =
    "http://guesswheresf.org/javascripts/bookmarklets/viewInGWW.js";
  script.type = "text/javascript";
  document.body.appendChild(script);
};
document.getElementById("viewInGWW").href =
  "javascript:(" + loadViewInGWW.toString() + ")();"
</script>

<p>To add "View in GWW" to your bookmarks,</p>

<h3>Firefox</h3>
<p>Either</p>
<ul>
  <li>drag the link to your bookmarks toolbar, or</li>
  <li>right-click (Windows) or control-click (Mac) on it and choose Bookmark This Link.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Internet Explorer</h3>
<ul>
<li>Right-click on the link</li>
<li>Choose Add to Favorites</li>
<li>If you see Security Alert, tell IE that yes, you want to continue. "View in GWW" does nothing unsafe; IE is just being cautious.</li>
<li>Change 'Create in' to Links, so the link goes to your Links toolbar</li>
<li>Choose Add</li>
</ul>

<p>To use "View in GWW", go to a Flickr photo page and click on or select "View
in GWW". You'll be taken to the photo's page in GWW.</p>

